# 📊 Customer & Sales Behavior Analysis | Online Retail

## Project Overview

Businesses collect thousands of sales transactions every day, but raw data alone doesn't help them make better decisions.

In this project, I analyzed an online retail dataset to understand **who the most valuable customers are, which products drive revenue, and how sales change throughout the year**. The goal was to turn over one million transaction records into meaningful business insights that could support marketing, inventory planning, and customer retention.

Using **Excel**, **MySQL**, and **Power BI**, I cleaned the data, performed SQL analysis, and built an interactive dashboard to help answer important business questions.

---

## Business Problem

The company wanted to answer several important questions:

* Which customers generate the most revenue?
* Which products sell the most and which generate the highest profit?
* Are there seasonal sales patterns?
* Which countries contribute the most revenue?
* Which products are frequently bought together?
* How can these insights improve business decisions?

Without this information, marketing campaigns, inventory planning, and customer retention strategies rely on assumptions instead of data.

---

